issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
I build OnnxRuntime (version 1.1.2 since it's the last supported by current Jetpack 4.3) on Jetson TX2 with TensorRT Execution Provider. But I'm having issues with running tiny YOLO models from https://github.com/onnx/models.
I'm able to run the tiny-YoloV2 model but with very low performances (no more than 3 FPS). 
With tiny-YoloV3 I got an error "Unsupported ONNX data type: BOOL (9)". See below for the full log.

Note the same models score well on OpenVino Execution Provider on my i7 laptop (CPU_FP32 current master branch). Moreover, I'm able to score the same tiny-YoloV2 model with a different runtime on TX2 with much better performances (more than 15 FPS).

Should I move to Jetpack 4.4 to make those models work?

Thanks a lot

Daniele
